The paper proposes a novel type of attractor neural network and discusses its application in theoretical neuroscience and computing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks, which are often used in machine learning and artificial intelligence applications, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of neuromorphic devices, which are often used in control systems and robotics, suggesting that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of complex algebraic computations, which may fall under the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
